Japanese Bought Net 440.4 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 
2011-08-03T23:55:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/japanese-bought-net-440-4-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended July 29 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 440.4 billion yen ($5.7 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 15.2 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 41.7 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 383.4 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 142.7 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 50.8 billion yen in stocks, and sold 354.8 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net sale 262.9
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  